m\": 803, \"to\": 937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 848, \"end\": 853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.881929075996736e-20, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 887, \"end\": 893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre_Palace\", \"score\": 0.9563967145716993, \"rank\": 0.04559121206067554, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre_Palace\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre_Palace\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A 6km river parade\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 821}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 837}, {\"ngram\": \"the Notre-Dame\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 878}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly 600,000 people\", \"from\": 901, \"to\": 922}, {\"ngram\": \"attendance\", \"from\": 926, \"to\": 936}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost 100 boats will carry an estimated 10,500 athletes along the city's main water artery, while spectators immerse themselves in the unique experience from the upper banks and lower quays.\", \"from\": 939, \"to\": 1130, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Almost 100 boats\", \"from\": 939, \"to\": 955}, {\"ngram\": \"an estimated 10,500 athletes\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 995}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's main water artery\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1030}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1048}, {\"ngram\": \"the unique experience\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1092}, {\"ngram\": \"the upper banks\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1113}, {\"ngram\": \"lower quays\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1129}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An estimated 1.5 billion viewers are expected to tune in to television broadcasts, which will begin at 6.30pm BST.\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1242, \"end\": 1245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.815916960167002e-15, \"text\": \"BST\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An estimated 1.5 billion viewers\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1164}, {\"ngram\": \"television broadcasts\", \"from\": 1192, \"to\": 1213}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With most anticipating this to be the largest Opening Ceremony in history - both in terms of audience and geographical coverage - the cultural tour, which begins at the Austerlitz Bridge, is designed to illustrate this year's Olympic slogan: \\\"Games Wide Open.\\\"\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1508, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the largest Opening Ceremony\", \"from\": 1282, \"to\": 1310}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1321}, {\"ngram\": \"terms\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1337}, {\"ngram\": \"audience\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1349}, {\"ngram\": \"geographical coverage\", \"from\": 1354, \"to\": 1375}, {\"ngram\": \"the cultural tour\", \"from\": 1378, \"to\": 1395}, {\"ngram\": \"the Austerlitz Bridge\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1434}, {\"ngram\": \"this year's Olympic slogan\", \"from\": 1462, \"to\": 1488}, {\"ngram\": \"Games Wide Open\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1506}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From the very beginning, planners wanted to make the opening ceremony accessible to the wider public, and so, with 222,000 free tickets up for grabs, everyone was given an equal opportunity to be part of the event.\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1724, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the very beginning\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1533}, {\"ngram\": \"planners\", \"from\": 1535, \"to\": 1543}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1579}, {\"ngram\": \"the wider public\", \"from\": 1594, \"to\": 1610}, {\"ngram\": \"222,000 free tickets\", \"from\": 1625, \"to\": 1645}, {\"ngram\": \"grabs\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1668}, {\"ngram\": \"an equal opportunity\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1699}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1706, \"to\": 1710}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1723}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And those who were unable to get their hands on a sought-after ticket will be catered for too, as 80 giant screens have been erected around Paris to amplify their viewing experience.\", \"from\": 1725, \"to\": 1907, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1865, \"end\": 1870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.942917939278926e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their hands\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1769}, {\"ngram\": \"a sought-after ticket\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1794}, {\"ngram\": \"80 giant screens\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 1839}, {\"ngram\": \"their viewing experience\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 1906}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, in order to deliver an event of such magnitude, head of the Paris 2024 organising committee Tony Estanguet has worked with a talented team of experts to help him through the process.\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 2096, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1974, \"end\": 1984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.879043861617326e-22, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 1917, \"to\": 1922}, {\"ngram\": \"an event\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 1942}, {\"ngram\": \"head\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1966}, {\"ngram\": \"a talented team\", \"from\": 2037, \"to\": 2052}, {\"ngram\": \"experts\", \"from\": 2056, \"to\": 2063}, {\"ngram\": \"the process\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2095}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since plans were unveiled three years ago, Thomas Jolly, a French theatre director and actor, has largely spearheaded the artistic element of this event.\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2251, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2141, \"end\": 2147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"score\": 0.9999708654910615, \"rank\": 1.8128508588287427e-05, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\"}, {\"begin\": 2157, \"end\": 2163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9912199043008066, \"rank\": 0.008468579667351305, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"plans\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2109}, {\"ngram\": \"actor\", \"from\": 2185, \"to\": 2190}, {\"ngram\": \"the artistic element\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2236}, {\"ngram\": \"this event\", \"from\": 2240, \"to\": 2250}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He promises to deliver a seismic and diverse show consisting of 3,000 artists, representing his nation's contrasting cultures by combining opera and rap pieces.\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2412, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a seismic and diverse show\", \"from\": 2275, \"to\": 2301}, {\"ngram\": \"3,000 artists\", \"from\": 2316, \"to\": 2329}, {\"ngram\": \"his nation's contrasting cultures\", \"from\": 2344, \"to\": 2377}, {\"ngram\": \"opera and rap pieces\", \"from\": 2391, \"to\": 2411}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"France is a story that never stops being constructed, deconstructed, and reconstructed.\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2415, \"end\": 2421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9996506331147424, \"rank\": 0.00024342417574772234, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a story\", \"from\": 2425, \"to\": 2432}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's alive, it remains alive,\\\" Jolly told Associated Press.\", \"from\": 2503, \"to\": 2562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2545, \"end\": 2561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.999869187936956, \"rank\": 0.00013082917719397515, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jolly\", \"from\": 2534, \"to\": 2539}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This responsibility was ambitious, complex, but magnificent for an artist.\\\"\", \"from\": 2563, \"to\": 2639, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This responsibility\", \"from\": 2564, \"to\": 2583}, {\"ngram\": \"an artist\", \"from\": 2628, \"to\": 2637}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sharing Jolly's vision, ceremonies choreographer Maud Le Pladec will lead 400 dancers out onto each bridge along the Seine, all kitted out with a wardrobe of unique costumes designed by French television presenter Daphne Burki.\", \"from\": 2641, \"to\": 2868, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2758, \"end\": 2763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.881929075996736e-20, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2827, \"end\": 2833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9912199043008066, \"rank\": 0.008468579667351305, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2855, \"end\": 2861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daphne\", \"score\": 0.7416233467881744, \"rank\": 0.3483933634938254, \"text\": \"Daphne\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daphne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daphne\"}, {\"begin\": 2862, \"end\": 2867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ormur\", \"score\": 0.9999999981641849, \"rank\": 1.8360039067145196e-09, \"text\": \"Burki\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ormur\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ormur\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jolly's vision\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2663}, {\"ngram\": \"choreographer Maud Le Pladec\", \"from\": 2676, \"to\": 2704}, {\"ngram\": \"400 dancers\", \"from\": 2715, \"to\": 2726}, {\"ngram\": \"each bridge\", \"from\": 2736, \"to\": 2747}, {\"ngram\": \"a wardrobe\", \"from\": 2785, \"to\": 2795}, {\"ngram\": \"unique costumes\", \"from\": 2799, \"to\": 2814}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With a strong emphasis on sustainability, Burki looks to make full use of vintage and upcycled clothes, mixed in with some newer creations.\", \"from\": 2869, \"to\": 3008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2911, \"end\": 2916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ormur\", \"score\": 0.9999999981641849, \"rank\": 1.8360039067145196e-09, \"text\": \"Burki\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ormur\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ormur\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a strong emphasis\", \"from\": 2874, \"to\": 2891}, {\"ngram\": \"sustainability\", \"from\": 2895, \"to\": 2909}, {\"ngram\": \"full use\", \"from\": 2931, \"to\": 2939}, {\"ngram\": \"vintage and upcycled clothes\", \"from\": 2943, \"to\": 2971}, {\"ngram\": \"some newer creations\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 3007}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is a unique opportunity to shed light on the talents of passionate designers I have been working with for over twenty years, emerging designers or renowned maisons, in the framework of daily TV broadcasts,\\\" Burki said.\", \"from\": 3010, \"to\": 3234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3223, \"end\": 3228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ormur\", \"score\": 0.9999999981641849, \"rank\": 1.8360039067145196e-09, \"text\": \"Burki\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ormur\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ormur\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a unique opportunity\", \"from\": 3019, \"to\": 3039}, {\"ngram\": \"light\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3053}, {\"ngram\": \"the talents\", \"from\": 3057, \"to\": 3068}, {\"ngram\": \"passionate designers\", \"from\": 3072, \"to\": 3092}, {\"ngram\": \"over twenty years\", \"from\": 3122, \"to\": 3139}, {\"ngram\": \"the framework\", \"from\": 3184, \"to\": 3197}, {\"ngram\": \"daily TV broadcasts\", \"from\": 3201, \"to\": 3220}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I intend to show the best of French culture and fashion, especially with the sumptuous backdrop that Paris and the Seine offer.\\\"\", \"from\": 3235, \"to\": 3364, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3265, \"end\": 3279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 3337, \"end\": 3342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.942917939278926e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3351, \"end\": 3356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.881929075996736e-20, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fashion\", \"from\": 3284, \"to\": 3291}, {\"ngram\": \"the sumptuous backdrop\", \"from\": 3309, \"to\": 3331}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In order for this ambitious project to be successfully carried out, though, it must be underpinned by a rigorous installation schedule, ensuring that health and safety measures are upheld.\", \"from\": 3366, \"to\": 3554, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 3369, \"to\": 3374}, {\"ngram\": \"this ambitious project\", \"from\": 3379, \"to\": 3401}, {\"ngram\": \"a rigorous installation schedule\", \"from\": 3468, \"to\": 3500}, {\"ngram\": \"health and safety measures\", \"from\": 3516, \"to\": 3542}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since 18 July, the upper and lower quays running alongside the Seine have been closed off to the general public, while access routes and walkways for local residents and businesses - as well as emergency and security services - have remained open.\", \"from\": 3556, \"to\": 3803, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3619, \"end\": 3624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.881929075996736e-20, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"18 July\", \"from\": 3562, \"to\": 3569}, {\"ngram\": \"the upper and lower quays\", \"from\": 3571, \"to\": 3596}, {\"ngram\": \"the general public\", \"from\": 3649, \"to\": 3667}, {\"ngram\": \"access routes\", \"from\": 3675, \"to\": 3688}, {\"ngram\": \"walkways\", \"from\": 3693, \"to\": 3701}, {\"ngram\": \"local residents\", \"from\": 3706, \"to\": 3721}, {\"ngram\": \"businesses\", \"from\": 3726, \"to\": 3736}, {\"ngram\": \"emergency and security services\", \"from\": 3750, \"to\": 3781}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Police officers have installed an anti-terrorism barrier, which is nearly four miles long, along the river banks.\", \"from\": 3804, \"to\"